3. Fine-Tuning Stage
Once your .tsv datasets are generated from the data processing step, and you have your pre-trained_model.bin, you can run the classifier to fine-tune the model:



		# Fine-tune the ET-BERT classifier
		python3 fine-tuning/run_classifier.py \
		    --pretrained_model_path models/pre-trained_model.bin \
		    --vocab_path models/encryptd_vocab.txt \
		    --train_path ../datasets/campus_source/dataset/train_dataset.tsv \
		    --dev_path ../datasets/campus_source/dataset/valid_dataset.tsv \
		    --test_path ../datasets/campus_source/dataset/test_dataset.tsv \
		    --epochs_num 10 \
		    --batch_size 32 \
		    --embedding word_pos_seg \
		    --encoder transformer \
		    --mask fully_visible \
		    --seq_length 128 \
		    --learning_rate 2e-5
		Use code with care. Learn more
		
4. Inference Stage
After fine-tuning is complete, you can use the resulting finetuned_model.bin to classify new, unlabeled traffic:

		# Run inference on unlabeled dataset
		python3 inference/run_classifier_infer.py \
		    --load_model_path models/finetuned_model.bin \
		    --vocab_path models/encryptd_vocab.txt \
		    --test_path ../datasets/campus_source/dataset/nolabel_test_dataset.tsv \
		    --prediction_path ../datasets/campus_source/dataset/prediction.tsv \
		    --labels_num 120 \
		    --embedding word_pos_seg \
		    --encoder transformer \
		    --mask fully_visible

(Note: Ensure you update --labels_num to match the exact number of traffic classes in your dataset).




